In [59]: 
def plot_mdist_by_term(students, term):
    df = students[students.TERMBNR == int(term)]
    counts = df.PMAJR.value_counts()
    counts = counts.reindex(all_majors, fill_value=0)
    num_undeclared = counts['UNDE']
    del counts['UNDE']
    
    width = 1.7
    indexes = np.arange(len(counts)) * width
    values = counts.values
    labels = counts.index

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(20,8))
    ax.bar(indexes, values, width)
    ax.set_xticks(indexes + width * 0.5)
    ax.set_xticklabels(labels, rotation=90)
    ax.set_yticks(np.arange(0, max(counts)+100, 100))
    ax.xaxis.grid(False)
    
    year = str(term)[:4]
    code = int(str(term)[4:])
    season = 'Spring' if code == 10 else 'Fall' if code == 70 else 'Summer'
    ax.set_title("Major Distribution of Declared Students in Term: %s %s" % (season, year))
    ax.set_ylabel("Number of Students")
    ax.set_xlabel("Major")

    fig.savefig("%d-major-dist.pdf" % term, bbox_inches="tight", dpi=300)
    plt.show(fig)
    return num_undeclared

from matplotlib.dates import YearLocator, MonthLocator, DateFormatter
import datetime
date1 = datetime.date(1995, 1, 1)
date2 = datetime.date(2004, 4, 12)

years = YearLocator()   # every year
months = MonthLocator()  # every month
yearsFmt = DateFormatter('%Y-%m')

unde = []
for k,v in undeclared.items():
    termbnr = str(k)
    year = int(termbnr[:4])
    season = termbnr[4:]
    month = 1 if season == '10' else 5 if season == '40' else 8
    day = 20 if season == '10' else 18 if season == '40' else 25
    date = datetime.date(year, month, day)
    unde.append({'date': matplotlib.dates.date2num(date), 'num_students': v})
    
unde_df = pd.DataFrame(unde)
unde_df = unde_df.sort(('date'), inplace=False)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9,6))
ax.plot_date(unde_df['date'], unde_df['num_students'], '-')

# format the ticks
ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(years)
ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(yearsFmt)
ax.xaxis.set_minor_locator(months)
ax.autoscale_view()

# set labels
ax.set_title("Number of Undeclared Students Over All Terms")
ax.set_ylabel("Number of Students")
ax.set_xlabel("Terms")

fig.autofmt_xdate()
fig.savefig("num-undeclared-over-terms.pdf", bbox_inches="tight", dpi=300)
plt.show()
